<br>
Now that I got that out of the way, I'm not really scared, I swear!<br>
<br>
I am guessing that a majority of the players are high level. It's really hard to delete a character that you got high and worked so hard on. Being a newb for a few levels I've noticed that my newb areas are pretty empty, which is fine, they dont' take long to get through. Generally I've noticed on other servers that &quot;roleplayers&quot; tend to level slower. Fine and dandy. Are the mid level dungeons/zones populated at all? <br>
<br>
Now I don't really roleplay too much. I really like the idea of 1 character, that's what attracted me to this server in the first place. But I do respect that some of you want to roleplay so I will play along, but if it gets to the point where I have to take the time to decifer what you are saying then welcome to ignore. IE. I think Ogre DUM Speak is about as bad as L337 d00d speakz. I like the fact that most everyone speaks in full words. Nothing is more annoying than the Sow PLZ TY YW conversations that occur in Everquest. <br>
<br>
I also like how everyone I've met so far seems to be pretty nice. I've been buffed up by strangers a couple of times. Some higher level shadow knight(i think) in my newbie yard accidentally ksed me on a snake or something and tried to give me 50pp. I visited the bazaar and bought an insanely cheap tunic, so if you see a lowbie Magician without a robe hunting in some lowbie area i'm not naked I got a shirt! <br>
<br>
Well that's about it from now, I guess what i'm trying to say is that I'm not a d00d but i'm not really a roleplayer, I'm somewhere in between and I hope to have some fun on this server.<br>
<br>
Peace,<br>
<br>
Scootypuff Jr. <br>
